ORIGINAL: Swedish furniture manufacturer IKEA has acquired Greengold Value Forests SRL, the owner of 33,600 hectares of forest land in Romania, from Luxembourg-registered investment company Greengold European Capital for an undisclosed amount, the buyer's legal advisor Wolf Theiss announced. According to Romanian business daily Ziarul Financiar, the transaction could be worth between EUR 70mn and EUR 130mn. The forest lands, consisting of about 900 plots, are located in the counties of Prahova, Buzau, Vrancea, Botosani and Bihor, in Romania's central and northeastern part, with a smaller concentration in the northwest. Through the acquisition IKEA has entered a new business, which will allow the group to secure access to sustainable managed wood raw material. The deal represents the largest forestry transaction in Romania up to date and IKEA has become the largest forest owner in the country. The buyer acted in the transaction through its Romanian newly established subsidiary IRI Investments SRL, which will manage the new business segment of the group. Greengold Value Forests SRL, founded in 2013, is engaged in logging and preparing the timber. IKEA, founded in 1943, is a large international group engaged in the production and sale of furniture. The company has operations in 42 countries, with a total of 315 stores and 147,000 co-workers worldwide. IKEA posted revenues of EUR 28.7bn for FY ended 31 August 2014. In Romania, IKEA's retail division operates a store located in northern Bucharest, which was opened in 2007. Recently, IKEA has bought a land plot of 13.7 hectares in eastern Bucharest to open a second store. IKEA works in Romania with over 20 suppliers, which produce sofas, armchairs, tables, chairs and others. IKEA Romania employs 470 and for 2014 it had a turnover of EUR 88mn. Greengold is an independent Swedish private equity firm specialised in timberland investments and management, focusing on Eastern Europe, Scandinavia and Eastern Africa. The firm is headed by former partners and employees in Romania of the U.S. University of Harvard. In January 2015, after charges of corruption, the University's investment division Harvard Management Co has decided to transfer some forests in Romania to Greengold. 108999 15/07/2015 巴西 2,204.2 MW wind and hydropower assets of Renova 收购 SunEdison Inc 美国 半导体及相关设备制造业 (334413); Renova Energia SA 风力发电 (221115); 风力发电 (221115) 383.31 (官方数据) 100 巴西 并购 　 　 否 资产收购; 战略收购 完成的 股票 　 　 　 Veirano Advogados; Akin Gump Strauss Hauer & Feld LLP BTG Pactual SA Tauil & Chequer Advogados; Mattos Filho, Veiga Filho, Marrey Jr. e Quiroga Advogados; Milbank, Tweed, Hadley & McCloy LLP 　 　 　 　 　 　 UPDATE: On 18 September 2015 Renova announced the conclusion of the deal. ORIGINAL: U.S. renewable energy development company SunEdison Inc has signed a definitive agreement to acquire 2,204.2 MW of operating wind, solar and hydropower assets from Brazilian peer Renova Energia SA for an enterprise value of BRL 13.4bn (USD 4.27mn). The buyer acted through its recently created subsidiary TerraForm Global Inc. The deal is part of a Third Party Right of First Offer (ROFO) signed on 07 May 2015 granting SunEdison the right to purchase up to 1,870 MW of renewable energy projects (Backlog) of Renova, of which 534 MW are operating projects and the remaining are projects still under development. Renova will receive the corresponding amount in shares of TerraForm Global based on the average market trading price in the 30-trading sessions prior to the closing date. The transaction is subject to the achievement of an Initial Public Offering (IPO) by TerraForm Global, the fulfillment of certain conditions precedent and attainment of regulatory approvals from the Brazilian Council for Economic Defense (CADE), the National Electric Energy Agency (ANEEL) and Brazilian electric utilities company Eletrobras SA. Renova Energia SA, created in 2001, specialises in the generation and sale of electric energy through alternative renewable sources, with a focus on wind energy generation, solar power and small hydroelectric plants. The company has a portfolio of energy projects with 2.3 GW of contracted installed capacity throughout Brazil, almost all of which from wind farms. Renova posted revenues of BRL 302.87mn (USD 112.7mn) and a net loss of BRL 35.72mn (USD 13.29mn) in 2014. The company is listed on the BM&FBovespa Stock Exchange. SunEdison Inc, established in 1984 and located in Belmont, California, develops, finances, installs and operates renewable power plants. It is the world's largest renewable energy development company. SunEdison has installations and manufacturing plants and 39 offices located throughout North America, Europe and Asia, and employs more than 6,000 people. SunEdison posted USD 2.48bn in revenues and a net loss of USD 1.18mn in 2014. The company is listed on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE). ______________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE: Em 18 de setembro de 2015 a Renova anunciou o fechamento da transação. O novo valor do negócio é BRL 1.477bn (USD 383.3) e inclui BRL 451mn (USD 117mn) pagos em cash e 20.33 mn de ações ordinárias avaliadas em USD 15 por ação, que totalizam BRL 1.026bn (USD 266.27mn). ORIGINAL: A fabricante norte-americana de tecnologia solar SunEdison Inc chegou a um acordo para adquirir 2,204.2 MW de activos eólicos e hidroeléctricos da homôloga brasileira Renova Energia SA por BRL 13.4bn (USD 4.27mn). O comprador actuou por intermédio da sua subsidiária TerraForm Global Inc. A transacção faz parte de um direito de primeira oferta (ROFO, em inglês) assinado em 7 de Maio de 2015, outorgando ' SunEdison o direito de compra de 1,870 MW de outros projectos (Backlog) da Renova, dos quais 534 MW correspondem a projectos operacionais e os restantes a projectos ainda em desenvolvimento. A Renova receberá o montante mencionado numa permuta de acções da Terraform Global. A transacção está sujeita ' concretização de uma Oferta Pública Inicial (IPO, em inglês) pela TerraForm Global, ao cumprimento de certas condições precedentes e ' obtenção de aprovações regulatórias por parte do Conselho Administrativo de Defesa Económica (CADE), da Agência Nacional de Energia Eléctrica (ANEEL) e da empresa brasileira de geração de energia eléctrica Eletrobrás. A Renova Energia SA, criada em 2001, é especializada na geração e comercialização de energia elétrica por meio de fontes alternativas e renováveis, com foco em parques eólicos, projetos de energia solar e pequenas centrais hidrelétricas. A empresa tem um portfólio de projetos de energia com 2.3 GW de capacidade instalada contratada ao redor do Brasil. A SunEdison Inc, criada em 1984, é especializada na fabricação e venda de tecnologia solar e no desenvolvimento, financiamento, instalação e operação de usinas de energia solar. A empresa tem centros de instalação e de fabricação e 39 escritórios localizados na América do Norte, Europa e Ásia, e emprega cerca de 6,300 pessoas. The funding will be used to grow Paktor's business in existing markets of Singapore, Indonesia, Malaysia, Thailand, Vietnam, and Taiwan, as well as to expand into new markets in Asia. The raised proceeds will go towards the company's product development, improving Paktor's existing set of app features by adding localised offerings, such as in-app gifting and group chats. The investment will support Paktor's ongoing strategy to become one of the largest global social dating brands, Joseph Phua, the company's co-founder and CEO, said. Paktor Pte. The dating app has currently over 6 million registered users and creates 15 million matches a month. Paktor is one of the most successful social networking apps for singles in Southeast Asia. Majuven, incorporated in 2011, is an early and growth stage venture capital focused on biomedical science, digital and sustainable technologies. ORIGINAL: Sub-Saharan Africa-focused diamond mining company Paragon Diamonds announced that it has agreed to acquire a 75% stake in the Mothae kimberlite project in Lesotho from Canadian peer Lucara Diamond Corp for USD 8.5mn. Paragon plans to polish and sell a selection of diamonds recovered from the project and Lucara will get 5% of the profits. These payments will continue for the processing of not less than 6.75 million tonnes of ore. Also, Lucara will get 5% of the profits achieved from the sale of rough diamonds not selected for polishing, as well as from the continued ore processing capped at 6.75-million tonnes. The Mothae project is located close to Paragon's Lemphane kimberlite project and the company said that it believes that it is appropriate to ensure that facilities on both projects are constructed simultaneously and thus at the lowest possible cost to benefit from economies of scale whilst adjusting the timescale for commencement of production of the enlarged asset portfolio to the third quarter of 2015. The Mothae kimberlite project covers an area of 24.7 km2 and has an indicated/inferred resources of 39 million tonnes at 2.7 carats per hundred tonnes (cpht) at USD 1,060 per carat. Paragon Diamonds is based in Guernsey and has several diamond projects in Lesotho, Botswana and Zambia. ORIGINAL: Brazilian steel manufacturer Gerdau SA announced the acquisition of minority interests in its local subsidiaries Gerdau Aços Longos S.A., Gerdau Açominas S.A., Gerdau Aços Especiais S.A. and Gerdau América Latina Participações S.A. from Brazilian financial institution Itaú Unibanco S.A. and Dutch steel products manufacturer ArcelorMittal S.A. for BRL 1.986bn (USD 633.02mn). ArcelorMittal acted through its affiliate ArcelorMittal Netherlands BV. Gerdau will acquire 4.77% in Aços Longos, 3.50% in Açominas, 2.39% in Aços Especiais and 4.90% in América Latina Participações. The purchase price will be paid through an initial cash payment of BRL 339mn. In addition, Gerdau will posteriorly transfer 30 million treasury preference shares of Gerdau in the amount of BRL 206mn; exchange of a share of a Non Standardized Credit Right Investment Fund in the amount of BRL 802mn; and installment payments due in 2016, 2017, 2019, 2021 and 2022, in the aggregate amount of BRL 639mn. The deal is part of the acquirer's broad reorganisation program aiming at unifying the operating companies in Brazil, consolidating the earning of dividends and facilitating access to capital markets. The transaction is subject to the fulfilment of certain conditions. Gerdau Açominas S.A., founded in 1966, is a steel manufacturing and distributing company based in Ouro Branco. Its main plant, which covers around 1,000 hectares, is located between the cities of Ouro Branco and Congonhas. It also has a port terminal in Vitoria. Gerdau Aços Especiais, founded in 1973, is a Porto Alegre-based steel production focused company. It is specialized in making long steel products for the car industry. It offers carbon, stainless, engineering, tool, and alloy steel products. Gerdau Aços Longos is engaged in construction services and production and processing of steel and steel products. It is based in Rio de Janeiro and was founded in 2005. Gerdau América Latina Participações S.A. was founded in 2005 and is based in Porto Alegre, Brazil. It operates as holding company. Gerdau S.A., founded in 1901, is one of the largest long steel manufacturers, recyclers, and suppliers of special steel in the world. The company operates industrial facilities with installed capacity of 25 million metric tons of steel per year, located in 14 countries in North and South America, Europe, and Asia, and engages more than 45,000 employees. Gerdau posted BRL 39.9bn (USD 18.5bn) in revenues and a net profit of BRL 1.6bn (USD 735.6mn) in 2013. The company is listed on the Sao Paulo, Madrid, and New York stock exchanges. ArcelorMittal S.A., founded in 1976, is a multinational steel and mining corporation with an annual production capacity of 119 million tons of steel products and iron ore and 245,000 employees across 60 countries. ArcelorMittal is listed on the Luxembourg, New York, Euronext and Madrid stock exchanges. The company is present in Latin America with industrial facilities with an annual installed capacity of eight million tons of steel in Brazil, Mexico, Argentina, Costa Rica and Trinidad and Tobago. Itau Unibanco Holding SA, established in 1944, is one of the largest Brazilian financial groups, specialized in retail, corporate, insurance, pension plans, private banking, investment banking, and wealth management services. The group has 4,100 branches in 23 countries on four continents and engages around 95,000 employees. Itau Unibanco Holding SA is listed on the BM&FBovespa, Buenos Aires (BCBA) and New York (NYSE) Stock Exchanges, and reached a net income of BRL 21.9bn (USD 8.15bn) in 2014. The buyer was an entity controlled by Russian tycoon Andrey Bokarev. The transaction value was not disclosed. According to an estimate of Mikhail Burmistrov, general director of INFOLine-Analitika agency, the entire share capital of Ust-Luga Oil could be worth around RUB 110-130bn (1.95-2.3bn), excluding the debt, RBC news agency reported. It is also in line with Gunvor's plans to divest its assets in the country (terminals, pipelines and coal mines) after its founder and former co-shareholder, Gennady Timchenko, was sanctioned by the U.S. authorities for close relations to Russia's president Vladimir Putin. In April 2015, Gunvor Group sold its 30% stake in Russian coking coal miner Kolmar to structures of Andrey Bokarev for an undisclosed amount. Ust-Luga Oil renders services related to reloading black (various grades of black oil-fuel) and light (petroleum, naphtha, diesel fuel) oil products from rail vehicles into sea tankers. The terminal is considered to be one of the largest rail-to-ship bulk facilities for petroleum products in the world with a throughput capacity of over 30 million metric tonnes per year. In 2014, the terminal handled 23.6 million tonnes of products. According to Gunvor, the investments in the terminal's construction were around USD 1bn. In 2014, Ust-Luga Oil generated sales of RUB 11.7bn (USD 311.3mn). Andrey Bokarev has investments in the sectors of coal mining and logistics, transportation and industrial processes. He is chairman and co-owner of Russia's second largest thermal coal producer Kuzbassrazrezugol, president and co-owner of rolling stock manufacturer Transmashholding and a minority shareholder in Russian rail cargo operator Transoil. ORIGINAL: U.S. insurance group Liberty Mutual Insurance Co has agreed to acquire Chilean non-life insurer Compania de Seguros Generales Penta-Security SA (Penta-Security) from Chilean investment holding firm Empresas Penta SA and Chilean financial group Grupo Security SA, the latter reported. Liberty Mutual will launch a tender offer for all the 10,931,152 Penta-Security shares. The U.S. firm will pay CLP 9,605 (USD 14.77) per share, which brings the deal value for the entire Penta-Security stake at almost CLP 105bn (USD 162mn). Under the agreement, Liberty will acquire 29.55% from Grupo Security and 70.01% from Empresas Penta, which have already agreed to divest their stakes. Liberty Mutual Insurance acted via Liberty International Holdings Inc, one of the group's four strategic business units. For its part, Grupo Security acted via its wholly-owned subsidiary Inversiones Seguros Security Ltda, while Empresas Penta acted via Banco Penta. Luis Bonell, president of Liberty International, said that with this acquisition the company further expands its presence in Chile, and that Penta-Security offers a strategic complement to its business in the country and the region. The transaction is subject to regulatory and other approvals. Last week, on 10 July 2015, Banco Penta announced it has agreed to sell part of its investment banking business, and its entire participation in local brokerage firm Penta Corredores de Bolsa SA, as well as in investment funds management company Penta Administradora General de Fondos SA (Penta AGF) to Grupo Security for an aggregate consideration of CLP 19.5bn (USD 30mn). On the same day, Banco Penta also reported it has agreed to sell its credit portfolio to local peer Banco de Chile for approximately CLP 576bn (USD 885mn). Compania de Seguros Generales Penta-Security offers property and casualty insurance products and services. The company reported net income of CLP 3.94bn (USD 6mn) and total assets of CLP 357.8bn (USD 551mn) for FY ended 31 December 2014. Liberty Mutual Insurance is a U.S.-based insurance company offering all types of insurance products with strong presence in Latin America and Asia. The company is owned by U.S. holding firm Liberty Mutual Holding Company Inc which posted total assets of USD 124.56bn as of 31 March 2015, and net income of USD 1.83bn for FY ended 31 December 2014. Grupo Security provides financial, investment, insurance and other related services. It is mainly focused on banking, factoring, insurance, asset management and real estate. It posted total assets of CLP 7.76tn (USD 12.04bn) as of 31 March 2015, and net income of CLP 61bn (USD 94.7mn) for FY ended 31 December 2014. The agreement is expected to strengthen the airlines' strategic alliance and provide Gol with cash. It follows a 2011 deal under which the two airlines reached an agreement after Delta invested USD 100mn for a 3% stake in Gol. The deal comes also as a result of a drop in Gol's shares by 60% this year, because of the Brazilian economic crisis. Gol Linhas Aereas, founded in 2001, is the largest low-cost airline in Latin America with a fleet of 139 Boeing 737 Next Generation aircrafts, offering 900 daily flights to 62 destinations in ten countries in South America, Caribbean and the United States under the Gol and Varig brands. The company also provides cargo logistic services between 3,500 cities in Brazil and eight abroad under the Gollog brand. Gol Linhas Aereas has 18,706 employees, and reached a turnover of BRL 9.8bn (USD 4.18bn) and a net loss of BRL 1.06mn (USD 452mn) in 2014. Delta Airlines provides scheduled air transportation for passengers and cargo throughout the United States and around the world. Its airline operations include aircraft maintenance, repair and overhaul (MRO), staffing services for third parties, among others. The company also produces and sells gasoline, diesel and jet fuel. Delta Airlines Inc generated revenues of USD 40.4bn and a net income of USD 659mn for FY ended 31 December 2014. FIP Volluto is managed by U.S. investment firm PineBridge Investments LLC. PGI, founded in 1994, is an international manufacturer and marketer of engineered materials, focused primarily on the production of nonwoven products for hygiene, medical, wipes, filtration and industrial applications. The company has 23 manufacturing facilities in 17 countries in the United States, Canada, Europe, Asia and Latin America, and some 4,000 employees. PGI had USD 77.6bn in assets under management as of 30 September 2015. ORIGINAL: Brazilian asset manager Vinci Partners Investimentos Ltda (Vinci) and the Canadian government owned pension fund management firm Public Sector Pension Investment Board (PSP Investments) have agreed to acquire a 30% share in Center Shopping Rio (Rio de Janeiro city, Rio de Janeiro state, Brazil) from local shopping centres management company BR Malls Participacoes SA (BR Malls). According to the buyer's legal adviser the transaction is valued at BRL 48.2mn (USD 12.43mn). Vinci and PSP Investments acted through their real estate investment management arms Vinci FII and BRL II, respectively. Vinci RII will receive 25% of the acquired stake while BRL II the other 75%. On 1 July, 2015 CADE approved the transaction. Center Shopping Rio, inaugurated in 2001, has a gross leasable area of 14,957 m2 and is comprised of 111 stores and 626 parking lots. The shopping centre receives over 3.72 million visitors per year. On the same day, Vinci CADE approved three more deals between Vinci, PSP and BR Malls - a 30% stake in West Shopping (Rio de Janeiro city, Rio de Janeiro state, Brazil) for BRL 113.2mn (USD 29.18mn), a 70% stake in Shopping Crystal Plaza (Curitiba city, Parana state, Brazil) for BRL 69mn (USD 17.79mn) and a 44% stake in Shopping Paralela (Salvador city, Bahia state, Brazil) for BRL 156.6mn (USD 40.38mn). Vinci, established in 2009 in Rio de Janeiro, is an alternative investment management and financial advisory firm with BRL 15bn (USD 3.87bn) in assets under management, allocated in private equity, credit, real estate, hedge and equity funds. The company operates offices in Rio de Janeiro, em Sao Paulo e Nova York and employs around 30,000 professionals. BR Malls Participacoes SA, established in 1949, focuses on planning, development and management of shopping malls. The company is the largest shopping mall operator in Brazil with equity interests in 51 shopping malls with own GLA of 961,500 m2, located in 17 Brazilian states, and a portfolio of three commercial real estate projects, currently under development, with own GLA of 134,600 m2. ORIGINAL: U.S. renewable energy development company SunEdison Inc has signed a definitive agreement to acquire Brazilian energy company Light SA's 15.87% stake in local clean energy company Renova Energia SA for USD 250mn. Subject of the deal are 50,561,797 common shares. The seller acted through its subsidiary Light Energia SA. The transaction follows SunEdison's Letter of Intent (LoI) from June 2015 stating its interest to acquiring a 16% stake in Renova. At the time the U.S. company acquired through its subsidiary TerraForm Global 336 MW of wind and hydropower assets of Renova. The transaction is dependent on the fulfillment of certain conditions precedent and attainment of regulatory approvals from the Brazilian Council for Economic Defense (CADE) and the National Electric Energy Agency (ANEEL). Renova Energia SA, created in 2001, specialises in the generation and sale of electric energy through alternative renewable sources, with a focus on wind energy generation, solar power and small hydroelectric plants. The company has a portfolio of energy projects with 2.3 GW of contracted installed capacity throughout Brazil, almost all of which from wind farms. Renova posted revenues of BRL 302.87mn (USD 112.7mn) and a net loss of BRL 35.72mn (USD 13.29mn) in 2014. The company is listed on the BM&FBovespa Stock Exchange. SunEdison Inc, established in 1984 and located in Belmont, California, develops, finances, installs and operates renewable power plants. It is the world's largest renewable energy development company. SunEdison has installations and manufacturing plants and 39 offices located throughout North America, Europe and Asia, and employs more than 6,000 people. SunEdison posted USD 2.48bn in revenues and a net loss of USD 1.18mn in 2014. The company is listed on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE). Light SA, founded in 1899, is a energy sector-focused holding company. Through its subsidiaries, the company engages in the generation, transmission, distribution, and commercialisation of electric power services in Brazil. It operates through the Power Distribution, Power Generation and Power Trading segments. Light posted BRL 9.23bn (USD 3.43bn) in revenues and a net profit of BRL 662.83mn (USD 246.6mn) in 2014. According to market sources, the deal aligns with GFG's strategy to find sustainable business partners with great growth potential in the emerging countries. Kanui Comércio Varejista Ltda, founded in 2011 in São Paulo, is an online sportswear fashion store operating nationwide. Its products focus on outdoors sportswear. Tricae, founded in 2011 in Sao Paulo by Brazilian entrepreneur Gustavo Furtado, specializes in the development and operation of an online store for products and accessories for babies, children and parents, such as strollers, clothes, shoes, toys, hygiene, health and beauty products. Global Fashion Group, founded in 2011, operates in 27 countries with a population of more than 2.5 billion people and whose combined fashion market is estimated at EUR 330bn (around USD 433bn). As of 30 June 2014, GFG had 4.6 million active customers. For the first six months of 2014, GFG websites had 353 million unique visitors and generated gross sales of EUR 436mn (USD 572mn). Since the launch of the five e-commerce companies, they have raised more than EUR 1bn (USD 1.31bn) in funding from various PE and VC firms including Kinnevik, Access Industries, Summit Partners, Verlinvest, Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan (OTPP), Tengelmann and others. The three largest shareholders of GFG are Kinnevik, Rocket Internet and Access Industries. _______________________________________________________________________________________________ O grupo de e-commerce de moda global focado nos mercados emergentes Grupo Global Fashion (GFG) concordou em adquirir as empresas brasileiras de varejo de moda on-line Kanui Comércio Varejista Ltda e Tricae Comércio Varejista Ltda por uma quantia não revelada, de acordo com fontes locais. A Tricae, fundada em 2011 em São Paulo pelo empresário brasileiro Gustavo Furtado, é especializada no desenvolvimento e operação de uma loja virtual que oferece produtos e acessórios para bebês, crianças e pais, tais como carrinhos, roupas, sapatos, brinquedos, produtos de higiene, saúde e beleza. A Global Fashion Group, fundada em 2011, opera em 27 países com uma população de mais de 2.5 mil milhões de pessoas e cujo mercado da moda combinado é estimado em EUR 330bn (cerca de USD 433bn). 108443 01/07/2015 美国 U.S. pork business of Cargill Inc 收购 JBS SA 巴西 畜禽屠宰及肉制品加工 (3116); Cargill Inc 食品制造 (311); 非耐用品批发 (422); 投资银行及其他金融投资活动 (523); 畜禽屠宰及肉制品加工 (3116) 1,450.00 (官方数据) 100 美国 并购 　 　 否 资产收购; 战略收购 完成的 现金 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 UPDATE: On 30 October 2015 JBS SA announced the completion of the transaction. ORIGINAL: Brazilian animal protein processing group JBS SA announced that it has agreed to acquire the U.S. pork business (Cargill Pork LLC) of foods major Cargill Inc for USD 1.45bn. JBS acted through its U.S.-based subsidiary Swift Pork Company. Cargill acted through its North American meat business-focused umbrella organisation Cargill Meat Solutions Corporation. The deal includes Cargill's U.S. business related to the breeding, purchase and slaughtering of pigs and the processing and sale of pork: two meat processing factories in Ottumwa, state of Iowa and in Beardstown, state of Illinois, five feeding facilities in the states of Missouri, Arkansas, Iowa and Texas, and four swine farms in the states of Arkansas, Oklahoma and Texas. The deal is in line with JBS's strategic long-term growth plans for products of high aggregated added-value. Closing is subject to customary regulatory approvals and the fulfilment of certain conditions precedent. In June 2015, JBS SA also announced the acquisition of Moy Park Holdings Europe Ltd, the U.K. unit of local counterpart Marfrig Alimentos SA, for an enterprise value of USD 1.5bn. JBS SA, established in 1953, is the largest animal protein processing company in the world. The group specialises in the processing of beef, pork, lamb and chicken, and in manufacturing and distribution of food, leather, products for pets, biodiesel, collagen, cans and cleaning products. JBS operates 301 production units in Brazil, Mexico, Argentina, Paraguay, Uruguay, the United States, Australia, Italy, China, and Russia, employing more than 185,000 people. JBS posted USD 47bn in revenues and a net profit of USD 895.4mn in 2014. The company is listed on the BM&FBovespa Stock Exchange. Cargill Inc, established in 1985 and headquartered in Minnetonka, Minnesota, U.S.A., is an international producer and marketer of food, agricultural, financial and industrial products and services. The company is present in 67 countries and employs roughly 152,000 employees. Cargill posted USD 134.9bn in revenues and a net profit of USD 1.87bn in 2014. __________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE: Em 30 de outubro de 2015 a JBS SA anunciou o fechamento do negócio. ORIGINAL: O grupo brasileiro de processamento de proteína animal JBS SA anunciou que chegou a um acordo para adquirir certos activos do negócio de suinicultura da multinacional norte-americana Cargill Inc por USD 1.45bn. A JBS actuou por intermédio da sua subsidiária norte-americana Swift Pork Company. A Cargill actuou por intermédio da sua 'organização guarda-chuva' norte-americana de carnes Cargill Meat Solutions Corporation. A transacção inclui activos de criação, compra e abate de suínos e ao processamento e venda de carne suína: duas fábricas de processamento de carne em Ottumwa, Iowa e Beardstown, Illinois, cinco fábricas de ração em Missouri, Arkansas, Iowa e Texas e quatro granjas de suínos em Arkansas, Oklahoma e Texas. A aquisição está em linha com os planos estratégicos da JBS está alinhada com a estratégia da JBS de longo prazo de crescimento em produtos com maior valor agregado, ampliando a base de clientes, tanto no mercado interno quanto em exportações. O fecho da operação está sujeito ao cumprimento de certas condições precedentes e a aprovações regulatórias habituais. A Moy Park Holdings Europe Ltd, criada em 2008 em Craigavon, Reino Unido,é um produtor de produtos aviários e comida convencional para grandes retalhistas e clientes do sector alimentar na Inglaterra, Irlanda, Holanda e França. A empresa teve receitas de GBP 1.4bn (USD 2.2bn) no período findo em 31 de Dezembro de 2014. A JBS SA, fundada em 1953, é a maior empresa de processamento de proteína animal no mundo. A companhia é especializada no processamento de carnes bovina, suína, ovina e de frango, fabricação e distribuição de alimentos, couro, produtos para animais de estimação, biodiesel, colágeno, latas e produtos de limpeza, e opera 301 unidades de produção no Brasil, México, Argentina, Paraguai, Uruguai, Estados Unidos, Austrália, Itália, China e Rússia, envolvendo mais de 185,000 colaboradores. A JBS está listada na Bolsa de Valores de São Paulo BM&FBovespa, e gerou um faturamento de USD 47bn e um lucro líquido de USD 895.4mn em 2014. A Cargill, fundada em 1985, é uma produtora e comercializadora internacional de alimentos, produtos e serviços agrícolas, financeiros e industriais. A empresa está presente em 67 países e emprega mais de 142,000 funcionários. The exact acquired stake was not disclosed. The raised funds will support PSafe's strategy to expand its position in the online safety market in Latin America, complement its product offering and increase its marketing initiatives, aiming to reach 100 million users in the next few years. PSafe, founded in 2011 in Rio de Janeiro by Brazilian entrepreneur Marcello de Melo and Brazilian technology company Grupo Xango, specialises in the development and implementation of cloud solutions in the field of online safety, such as antivirus software, security identifier, PC's optimiser and cloud storage platforms. The company has more than 20 million average monthly users. Qihoo, established in 2005, engages in the development, management and sale of internet and mobile security and optimisation products, and internet browsers under the brands of 360 Anti-Virus, 360 Mobile Safe and 360 Safe Browser. The company has more than 657 million monthly active users, mainly in China. The company is listed on the New York Stock Exchange. Redpoint is a private equity and venture capital firm, specialised in investments in seed, early stage and growing companies, operating in the consumer internet, e-commerce, mobile, media and cloud technologies segments. Since its foundation in 1999, the company has raised approximately USD 3.4bn in capital and has invested in nearly 374 enterprises in North America, Asia, and Latin America. Pinnacle Ventures, founded in 2002, is a venture capital firm, specialised in mid to late equity investments and growth capital loans in companies from the consumer technology, e-commerce, internet and digital media, software, medical devices and healthcare, and mobile sectors in North America, Latin America and Europe. ________________________________________________________________________________________________ A desenvolvedora brasileira de software antivírus PSafe Tecnologia SA anunciou que recebeu um segundo aporte de USD 30mn da prestadora chinesa de serviços de segurança online Qihoo 360 Technology Co Ltd e das empresas norte-americanas de capital de risco Redpoint Ventures e Pinnacle Ventures. O tamanho da participação adquirida não foi divulgado. Os recursos captados vão apoiar a estratégia da PSafe para expandir sua posição no mercado de segurança online na América Latina, complementar sua oferta de produtos e aumentar suas iniciativas de marketing, com o objetivo de alcançar 100 milhões de usuários nos próximos anos. A empresa tem mais de 20 milhões de usuários médios mensais. A Qihoo, fundada em 2005, atua no desenvolvimento, gestão e venda de produtos de segurança na internet para PC e dispositivos móveis, produtos de otimização e internet navegadores sob as marcas 360 Anti-Virus, 360 Mobile Safe e 360 Safe Browser. A empresa tem mais de 657 milhões de usuários ativos mensais, principalmente na China. A empresa está listada na Bolsa de Valores de Nova York. A Redpoint é uma companhia de captial de risco e investimento em participações, especializada em capital semente, investimentos em empresas em fase inicial e em fase de crescimento que atuam nos setores de internet, comércio eletrônico, mobilidade, mídia e tecnologias em nuvem. Desde sua fundação em 1999, a companhia levantou cerca de USD 3.4bn de capital e investiu em 374 empresas na América do Norte, Ásia e América Latina. A Pinnacle Ventures, criada em 2002, é uma empresa de capital de risco, especializada em investimentos de capital e empréstimos para crescimento para empresas em estagios de expansão e maturidade dos setores de tecnologia da informação, comércio electrónico, internet e mídia digital, mobile, software, saúde e dispositivos médicos na América do Norte, América Latina e Europa. 2015.10.08 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 负值 　 　 来源 1

ORIGINAL: Canadian telecommunications software products and services provider Redknee Solutions Inc has acquired Brazilian software company Orga Systems Brasil Informatica Ltda from German charging and billing solutions provider Orga Systems GmbH, the buyer's legal advisor announced. The buyer acted through its Brazilian subsidiary, the holding company Iron House Empreendimentos S.A. The transaction is part of a global deal involving the acquisition of Orga Systems' employees, customers, partners and software portfolio by Redknee for total proceeds of EUR 38mn (USD 43.1mn). The deal follows Orga Systems' filing for bankruptcy in March 2015. Orga Systems GmbH, founded in 2003 and headquartered in Paderborn, Germany, is a software vendor for convergent charging and billing solutions with an international customer base in telecommunications, utilities and automotive markets. The company operates in 10 additional locations in Berlin, Germany, Buenos Aires, Argentina, Dubai, United Arab Emirates, Istanbul, Turkey, Kiev, Ukraine, Moscow, Russia, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, Kolkata, India,, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil and Rome, Italy. Redknee Solutions Inc, founded in 1999 in Toronto, Ontario, Canada,is a leading global provider of innovative communication software products, solutions and services. The company's products enable service providers to monetise new services, business models and content and to deliver a connected customer experience - through either SaaS or on-premise based solutions. ORIGINAL: Singapore-listed toll road operator China Merchants Holdings (Pacific) Ltd (CMHP) will acquire Yangping Expressway in China from local conglomerate company Shenzhen Yitian Group Co. Ltd. and from Shenzhen Ruiwo Yilai Real Estate Development Co. Ltd. for a total consideration of CNY 848.0mn (USD 138.4mn), the former announced in a bourse filling. The deal includes the acquisition of Guangxi Huatong Expressway Co. Ltd., the company which owns the rights to operate Yangping Expressway. Through the same announcement, CMHP said it will acquire also Guixing Expressway and Guiyang Expressway. The three expressways are located in the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, southern China. The acquisition is subject to certain conditions precedent and regulatory approval. The consideration will be funded by CMHP with bank borrowings and/or with the issuance of new shares. Through the acquisitions, CMHP will expand its geographical coverage into the fast developing Guangxi region and will strengthen its position as a leading toll road operator in the transportation infrastructure sector of China. Following the three acquisitions, CMHP's toll road portfolio will comprise eight expressways in China and their total length will increase to around 575 km, from the current length of 415 km. Yangping Expressway is a 39.52 km four-lane carriageway (dual-2) located at the eastern area of Guilin Municipality, connecting Yangshuo County with Pingle County, in the north-east of Guangxi. It is part of G65 China's National Expressway System. The toll operating rights for the Yangping Expressway were granted by local authorities for a period of 29 years, from 2008 until 2037. CMHP is a leading toll road company investing in and managing toll roads in China. It is also involved in property development in New Zealand. Based in Singapore, the company is a member of China Merchants Group and is its largest company in Southeast Asia. CMHP posted net sales of HKD 1.99bn (USD 257.2mn) for 2014. ORIGINAL: French oil and gas major Total SA has agreed to sell to Gazprom its 25% stake in Swiss-headquartered company Shtokman Development AG, engaged in the first stage development of large Shtokman gas condensate field in the Barents Sea, Vedomosti daily reported, citing three sources close to the deal parties. Total SA reportedly decided to pull out of the project following a failure of the project participants to sign an investment agreement whose term expired in August 2012. At that time, Gazprom announced that the Shtokman project would be stalled for an indefinite period. In September 2012, Norwegian oil major Statoil first sold its stake of 24% to Gazprom which consolidated a 75% interest. Total SA then stayed in the project but incurred losses. Shtokman gas condensate field lies in the centre of a shelf zone of the Russian sector of the Barents Sea, about 600 kilometres north-east from Murmansk. The deposit holds C1+C2 reserves of 3.8 trillion cubic meters of gas and around 37 million tons of gas condensate. Phase 1 of the development is estimated to provide production of 23.7 billion cubic meters of natural gas per annum. Gazprom is a global energy company whose major business lines are geological exploration, production, transportation, storage, processing and sales of gas, gas condensate and oil, sales of gas as a vehicle fuel as well as generation and marketing of heat and electric power, according to the 2014 financial report of Volzhskaya TGK which unites the generating assets of IES-Holding. 2015.07.29 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 负值 　 　 来源 1

ORIGINAL: U.S.-based automotive industry multinational Affinia Group Holdings Inc announced the sale of its Brazilian subsidiary Affinia Automotiva Ltda to local distributors. According to market sources, Brazilian auto parts dealer Distribuidora Automotiva SA, formed a consortium with other local distributors to purchase the industrial part of the business of the target. In addition, Brazilian industrial holding Comolatti Group will acquire the target's shock-absorber factory in São Paulo. The deal value is estimated to be in the amount of BRL 361.3mn (USD 116.74mn). Affinia Automotiva is part of Affinia South America (ASA) and is responsible for approximately 90% of its sales. The transaction is part of the seller's divestiture plan to reduce its debt levels and strengthen its balance sheet. The company plans to focus, from now on, on its global filtration segment. The deal is subject to regulatory approval and customary closing conditions and is expected to close in the second half of 2015. Affinia Automotiva Ltda, established in 2004, specialises in the manufacture and distribution of auto parts for the aftermarket in Brazil. The company took over the operations of the brands Nakata, Wix and Spicer since it began its activities. It has sold more than 115 million parts in Brazil. Distribuidora Automotiva, created in 1988 as the auto parts retailer of local industrial holding Comolatti Group, operates a network of 22 distribution centers for auto parts, tires, and accessories in Brazil under the brands of Sama, Laguna, and Matrix. Comolatti Group, founded in 1956, is an industrial holding with interests in the vehicles and auto parts distribution, the real estate and the food sectors, and engages over 4,000 employees. In the vehicle sales segment, the group operates with the concessionaires Tiete and Cofipe, which are licensed re-sellers of Man, Volkswagen, and Iveco brands in Brazil. Affinia Group Holdings Inc, established in 2004 in Ann Arbor, Michigan, USA, designs, manufactures, markets, and distributes a range of aftermarket products in North America, South America, Europe, and Asia. Its products include routine maintenance products and wear products. Affinia's products are marketed under various brands, including WIX, Raybestos, Nakata, Brake-Pro, Filtron, AIMCO, and McQuay-Norris. It has over 11,000 employees spread throughout 23 offices worldwide. Affinia posted revenues of USD 1.39bn and a net profit of USD 82mn in 2014. ______________________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE: Em 4 de novembro de 2015, a Affinia anunciou o fechamento do negócio. ORIGINAL: Brazilian animal protein processing group JBS SA has agreed to acquire Moy Park Holdings Europe Ltd, the U.K. unit of local counterpart Marfrig Alimentos SA, for an enterprise value of USD 1.5bn, both companies announced. JBS will pay USD 1.19bn in cash and also assume the net debt of Moy Park of GBP 200mn (around USD 318mn). The acquisition is in line with JBS's strategic plans to solidify its expansion into European markets. The company said that the deal is an important step towards growing its portfolio of prepared and convenient products with high value added. Closing is subject to customary regulatory approvals and the fulfilment of certain conditions precedent. The deal is expected to complete by the end of 2015. Moy Park Holdings Europe Ltd, created in 2008 in Craigavon, U.K., is a provider of farmed poultry and convenience food products to major retailers and large foodservice customers throughout Britain, Ireland, the Netherlands and France. The company had revenues of GBP 1.4bn (USD 2.2bn) for FY 2014. JBS SA, established in 1953, is the largest animal protein processing company in the world. The group specializes in the processing of beef, pork, lamb and chicken, and in manufacturing and distribution of food, leather, products for pets, biodiesel, collagen, cans and cleaning products. JBS operates 301 production units in Brazil, Mexico, Argentina, Paraguay, Uruguay, the United States, Australia, Italy, China, and Russia, employing more than 185,000 people. JBS posted USD 47b in revenues and a net profit of USD 895.4mn in 2014. The company is listed on the BM&FBovespa Stock Exchange. Marfrig Alimentos SA, founded in 1986, is a multinational animal protein and processed foods group, specialized in the processing, production, and sale of beef, pork, lamb and poultry, pasta and similar foods, ready-to-eat meals, frozen vegetables, and semi-finished and finished leather. The company operates 183 processing plants, distribution centers, feedlots and offices in 17 countries in South America, North America, Europe, Asia and Africa, and has a daily slaughtering capacity of 20,730 head of cattle, 3.7 million chickens, 11,179 head of pork, 41,000 turkeys and 11,900 lambs, and a monthly production capacity of 120,667 metric tons of processed food and 294,000 leather articles. Marfrig posted revenues of BRL 21.07bn (USD 7.84bn) and a net loss of BRL 720.3mn (USD 268.06mn) in 2014. It has total installed capacity of 230 MW. The company employs 90 people, and posted revenues of PLN 46.6mn (EUR 11.1mn) and net profit of PLN 0.39mn (EUR 0.09mn) in 2013. Veolia operates in Poland since 1994. The company is the largest operator of district heating networks in Poland, active in over 40 cities. It employs 5,000 people. Veolia Environnement is a provider of environmental management services to public authorities, industrial and commercial clients worldwide. ORIGINAL: Spanish hotel and travel agency group Barcelo Corporacion Empresarial announced that it has agreed to acquire the 57.5% it still does not own in Latin America-focused hotel operator Occidental Hoteles Management from Spanish financial services group BBVA. Financial details on the deal were not disclosed. Barcelo said that the purchase represents a very important step for its growth strategy in Latin America. In May 2015, Barcelo announced the purchase of a 42.5% stake in Occidental Hoteles. Occidental Hoteles manages a total of 11 hotels in Mexico, the Dominican Republic, Costa Rica and Aruba. The hotels have some 4,000 rooms. Barcelo Corporacion Empresarial was founded in 1931 and currently has more than 140 hotels in 17 countries and 505 travel agencies in 22 countries. The group employs some 23,000 people and has been owned by the Barcelo family for three generations. 2016.03.29 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 负值 　 　 来源 1 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　
107950 16/06/2015 巴西 Blue Ocean Agencia Maritima Ltda 收购 Archer Daniels Midland Co (ADM); Norton Lilly International Inc 美国 食品制造 (311); 食品杂货批发 (4224); 交通运输辅助活动 (488); 　 交通运输辅助活动 (488) 　 　 　 　 并购 　 　 否 战略收购 已公布 现金 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 U.S. food-processing and commodities-trading group Archer Daniels Midland Co (ADM) and U.S. shipping company Norton Lilly International LLC have agreed to acquire Brazilian port and shipping agency Blue Ocean Agencia Maritima Ltda for an undisclosed amount. The buyers acted through their steamship agency joint venture Agri Port Services LLC. The acquisition is part of the buyer's strategy to expand their logistics offerings in Brazil as well as to provide Agri Port with a contact point for customers in North and South America. According to market sources, ADM already holds a minority stake in Blue Ocean. Blue Ocean Agencia Maritima Ltda, based in Santos, state of São Paulo, provides assistance to oceangoing vessels at ports throughout Brazil and maintains offices in the strategic ports of Santos and Paranaguá. The company serves as a shipping agent for both inbound and outbound vessels, coordinating vessel clearance, loading/discharging operations, vessel logistics and support, vessel resupply, and cargo and customs documentation. Archer Daniels Midland Co (ADM), founded in 1898 and based in Chicago, Illinois, procures, transports, stores, processes, and merchandises agricultural commodities and products. The company operates in the following segments: Oilseeds Processing, Corn Processing, Agricultural Services, and Wild Flavors and Specialty Ingredients. ADM operates more than 270 plants and 420 crop procurement facilities worldwide, where cereal grains and oilseeds are processed into products used in food, beverage, nutraceutical, industrial, and animal feed markets worldwide. It employs over 34,000 people. ADM is listed on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) and recorded revenues of USD 81.2bn in 2014. Norton Lilly International Inc, established in 1841, through its subsidiaries, engages in the business of ship agency services, logistics, brokerage, vessel planning and other marine activities. The company's services encompasses all types of liner, bulker, tanker, reefer and passenger vessels, and handles over 20,000 port calls per year. Norton has 37 offices in various cities in the U.S. and abroad in Canada, Panama, Mexico, the Caribbean, South America and the Pacific Islands. ____________________________________________________________________________________ A Archer Daniels Midland (ADM), empresa americana de processamento de alimentos e comércio de matérias-primas, e a empresa de transporte marítimo de mercadorias Norton Lilly International LLC concordaram em adquirir a homóloga brasileira Blue Ocean Agencia Maritima Ltda, por uma quantia não revelada. Os adquirentes actuaram por intermédio da sua joint venture Agri Port Services LLC. A aquisição está em linha com a estratégia dos adquirentes de expandir as suas ofertas logísticas no Brasil e paralelamente providenciar a Agri Port com um ponto de contacto para os seus clientes da América do Norte e do Sul. De acordo com fontes de mercado, a ADM já detém um participação minoritária na empresa-alvo. A Blue Ocean Agência Marítima Ltda, com sede em Santos, Estado de São Paulo, presta assistência a navios oceânicos em portos em todo o Brasil e mantém escritórios nos portos estratégicos de Santos e Paranaguá. A empresa serve como um agente de transporte para ambos os navios de entrada e saída, coordenando apuramentos dos navios, cargas e descargas, logística e apoio de navios, navios de reabastecimento, e carga e documentação aduaneira. A Archer Daniels Midland Co (ADM), fundada em 1898 e com sede em Chicago, Illinois, adquire, transporta, armazena, processa, e vende commodities agrícolas e produtos. A empresa atua nos seguintes segmentos: Processamento de Sementes Oleaginosas, Processamento de Milho, Serviços Agrícolas, Sabores Selvagens e Ingredientes de Especialidades. A ADM opera mais de 270 plantas e 420 instalações de adjudicação de contratos das culturas em todo o mundo, onde os grãos de cereais e oleaginosas são transformados em produtos utilizados nos mercados de alimentos, de bebidas, nutracêuticos, industriais e de alimentos para animais em todo o mundo. Emprega mais de 34,000 pessoas. A ADM está listada na New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) e registou receitas de USD 81.2bn em 2014. A Norton Lilly International Inc, fundada em 1841, através de suas subsidiárias, se engaja no negócio de serviços de agência de navio, logística, corretagem, planejamento navio e outras actividades marítimas. Os serviços da empresa abrangem todo os tipos de navios de linha, bulker, petroleiros, frigoríficos e de passageiros e lidam com mais de 20,000 escalas por ano. 107943 16/06/2015 俄罗斯 Aeroxo 少数股权购买 Eldar Razroev - private investor; I2BF Global Ventures 俄罗斯; 美国 基金、信托及其他金融工具 (525); 　 　 航空航天器械制造 (3364) 1 (官方数据) 　 　 并购 　 进入 否 财务收购 完成的 现金 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 Russian drones manufacturer Aeroxo has raised USD 1mn of financing from its co-founder Eldar Razroev and international clean technology venture capital firm I2BF Global Ventures, Firrma.ru reported, citing sources from I2BF. Each of the investors contributed USD 500,000. The exact stake acquired was not disclosed. The managing partner of I2BF Global Ventures, Ilya Golubovich, holds 40% in Aeroxo. He explained, as cited by Firrma.ru, that part of this interest was obtained at the creation of the company and part - as a result of the above funding. In addition, Aeroxo also received RUB 5mn (USD 91,053) from Russian new technologies development fund Skolkovo Fund. All the proceeds will be used for further development of the drone technology, the applications and the playload system, as well as for the completion of a cloud platform for processing, storage and visualisation of data. Aeroxo was founded in 2014. The company produces long-range unmanned aerial systems based on the tilt-rotor UAV technology. Aeroxo is headquartered in Moscow but also has two representative offices in Kazan (Tatarstan) and New York (USA). Established in 2005, I2BF Global Ventures manages USD 400 million across four venture capital vehicles. The fund targets innovative and competitive companies across the clean technology community, biotechnology, materials science, IT and space technology sectors. Apart from its head team in New York, I2BF has also representative offices in London, Moscow and Astana. 2015.06.17 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 负值
